*Css can be load at any part of the html.

NOTE: Only use rel=**stylesheet** it is default

# Properties:

1. Text-align : center/left/right/justify/start/;
   color: color name;

2. text-decoration-line: line-through/overline/underline/none; (strike)

text-decoration-color:(change the underline color)
text-decoration-style: solid/dashed/wavy/double.
text-decoration-thickness; 2px;

# Short-hand property:

##### text-decoration: underline color double 1px;

*To remove the line text-decoration-none;

3. text-transform: uppercase/lowercase/capitalize/none;

4. text-shadow: 3 px 0px 2px (right, top-bottom, blur, 2px 2px 3 px green (multiple shadows)) color

5. letter-spacing: 2px -2px ;(letter spacing, decreasing space.)

6. Word-spacing: 5px; ( word spacing )

7. text-indent: 10px; (space on the beginning of the paragraph)( work for block level elements)

8. line-height: ; ( line between words)

comment <out-> for HJHTML <!---->
For css - /*----*/

---------------------------------------------------

**To style particular paragraph :**

we use ID-- represents #(ID selector):
using element-- element selector.

To style for 2 paragraphs at same style:

We use Class --represents . (class selector);

Inline css has the highest priority
Id- will have more priority than class 
Class- will have more priority than elements.
-------------------------------------------------------------

# CSS selectors:

1. CSS element selector--Element tag name
2. CSS ID selector--#IDname
3. CSS Class selector---.classname
4. CSS Universal selector--*(selects all HTML elements)
5. CSS grouping selector--(selects all the HTML elements with same style)
6. Css element.class-- p.intro( selects only p elements with class into)
7. css element,element--div, p (Selects all <div>, p elements )


